blogs.title: Major Operation to Rescue Blind Stray Dog
blogs.content: In a compassionate and high stakes rescue mission, animal welfare volunteers in Chennai recently carried out a major operation to save a blind stray dog found in dire condition. The rescue underscores the ongoing challenges of caring for vulnerable animals on city streets.
blogs.author: Himani

blogs.title: Keep Your Cat Purring
blogs.content:
Cats love routine and comfort. Keep their litter box clean, provide cozy resting spots, and offer a scratching post to protect your furniture.
Play with them daily  even short sessions build trust and reduce stress.
And dont forget slow blinks  your cats way of saying I love you.
blogs.author: Ananya Roy

blogs.title: Happy and Healthy Pet Birds
blogs.content:
Birds need mental stimulation as much as physical care. Give them colorful toys, mirrors, and perches of different textures.
Let them out of the cage (safely) to stretch their wings.
Clean food and water daily, and talk to them often  birds love attention!
blogs.author: Saanvi Patel

blogs.title: Easy Fish Tank Care
blogs.content:
Keeping fish is peaceful and rewarding.
Maintain clean water by changing 20% weekly and avoid overfeeding  leftover food pollutes the tank.
Check water temperature and pH regularly.
Healthy fish swim actively and have bright, clear colors  a sign of perfect care.
blogs.author: Rohan Desai

blogs.title: Simple Tips for Happy Dogs
blogs.content:
Dogs need more than food and walks  they crave love and attention. Spend time playing fetch or taking daily strolls to keep them active.
Regular grooming, vaccinations, and dental care prevent common health issues.
A happy dog is one that feels loved, exercised, and cared for every single day.
blogs.author: Riya Mehta

blogs.title: Caring for Your Rabbit
blogs.content:
Rabbits are gentle, social animals that need space to hop and explore.
Feed them hay, fresh greens, and clean water daily.
Avoid keeping them alone  rabbits thrive with companionship.
Regular brushing and nail trims keep them healthy and comfortable.
blogs.author: Ashnoor Malik
